eloquent /ˈɛləkwənt/

1. ADJ Speech or writing that is eloquent is well expressed and effective in persuading people. 雄辩的; 有说服力的 

例： I heard him make a very eloquent speech at that dinner. 我听他在那次晚餐上做了一次很有说服力的演说。 

2. eloquence N-UNCOUNT 雄辩力; 说服力 

例： ...the eloquence of his prose. …他散文的说服力。 

3. ADJ A person who is eloquent is good at speaking and able to persuade people. 能言善辩的 [表赞许] 

例： He was eloquent about his love of books. 他善于谈论他对书籍的热爱。 

4. eloquence N-UNCOUNT 能言善辩 

例： She can speak with an eloquence that is almost inspirational. 她能用一种近乎激发灵感的口才发言。

